                             ===Patch Result===                                                                                                                                                                  
                             ERROR: libFuzzer: timeout                                                                                                                                                           
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             ===Issue===                                                                                                                                                                         
                             ERROR: libFuzzer: timeout                                                                                                                                                           
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             ===Evaluation Report===                                                                                                                                                             
                             # Evaluation Report                                                                                                                                                                 
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             ## Summary                                                                                                                                                                          
                             The initial issue was that fuzzing the Apache POI HSLF code with libFuzzer resulted in a timeout rather than a crash or exception. A patch was applied in                           
                             `HSLFSlideShowImpl.java` to simplify the handling of repeated user edit atom offsets: the repair-and-throw logic was removed and replaced with a single warning                   
                             log and a loop break. After applying this patch, the fuzzer still reported a timeout.                                                                                               
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             ## Description                                                                                                                                                                      
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             Initial Issue                                                                                                                                                                       
                             - When running libFuzzer against the HSLF (PowerPoint) parser in Apache POI, the fuzzer did not trigger an immediate exception or crash. Instead, it hung in a loop                 
                             until the fuzzers timeout threshold was reached, yielding `ERROR: libFuzzer: timeout`.                                                                                             
                             - No stack trace or exception was emitted; the fuzzer simply stopped after exceeding its time budget, indicating a potential infinite or very long loop in the                      
                             parsing code.                                                                                                                                                                       
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             Patch Attempt                                                                                                                                                                       
                             - File modified: `poi-scratchpad/src/main/java/org/apache/poi/hslf/usermodel/HSLFSlideShowImpl.java`                                                                                
                             - Location: around the logic that handles user edit atom offsets in the record parsing loop (originally lines 344365).                                                           
                             - Original code detected when a new `usrOffset` was already in the `recordMap`. It then attempted to guess a corrected offset (`recordMap.firstKey() - 36`),                        
                             validated the record headers, and either repaired the atom or threw `CorruptPowerPointFileException`.                                                                               
                             - Patched code simply logs a warning when a repeated offset is seen, then executes `break;` to exit the loop and continue parsing.                                                  
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             Unified Diff of Key Changes:                                                                                                                                                        
                             ```                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             --- a/poi-scratchpad/src/main/java/org/apache/poi/hslf/usermodel/HSLFSlideShowImpl.java                                                                                             
                             +++ b/poi-scratchpad/src/main/java/org/apache/poi/hslf/usermodel/HSLFSlideShowImpl.java                                                                                             
                             @@ -344,21 +344,10 @@                                                                                                                                                               
                                          usrOffset = usr.getLastUserEditAtomOffset();                                                                                                                           
                             -            // check for corrupted user edit atom and try to repair it                                                                                                             
                             -            // if the next user edit atom offset is already known, we would go into an endless loop                                                                                
                             +            // detect loops in user edit atom offsets and break to avoid infinite loop                                                                                             
                                          if (usrOffset > 0 && recordMap.containsKey(usrOffset)) {                                                                                                               
                             -                // a user edit atom is usually located 36 byte before the smallest known record offset                                                                             
                             -                usrOffset = recordMap.firstKey() - 36;                                                                                                                             
                             -                // check that we really are located on a user edit atom                                                                                                            
                             -                int ver_inst = LittleEndian.getUShort(docstream, usrOffset);                                                                                                       
                             -                int type = LittleEndian.getUShort(docstream, usrOffset + 2);                                                                                                       
                             -                int len = LittleEndian.getInt(docstream, usrOffset + 4);                                                                                                           
                             -                if (ver_inst == 0 && type == 4085 && (len == 0x1C || len == 0x20)) {                                                                                               
                             -                    LOG.atWarn().log("Repairing invalid user edit atom");                                                                                                          
                             -                    usr.setLastUserEditAtomOffset(usrOffset);                                                                                                                      
                             -                } else {                                                                                                                                                           
                             -                    throw new CorruptPowerPointFileException("Powerpoint document contains invalid user edit atom");                                                               
                             -                }                                                                                                                                                                  
                             +                LOG.atWarn().log(                                                                                                                                                  
                             +                  "Detected loop in user edit atoms at offset {}, breaking to avoid infinite loop",                                                                                
                             +                  usrOffset);                                                                                                                                                      
                             +                break;                                                                                                                                                             
                                          }                                                                                                                                                                      
                             ```                                                                                                                                                                                 
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             Result After Patch                                                                                                                                                                  
                             - A subsequent fuzzing run still ended with `ERROR: libFuzzer: timeout`, indicating that the change did not eliminate the long-running or infinite loop condition.                  
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             Further Areas for Investigation                                                                                                                                                     
                             - The looping and offset-tracking logic in `HSLFSlideShowImpl`, particularly:                                                                                                       
                                The main record-parsing loop where `recordMap` is updated.                                                                                                                      
                                All branches that compute or reset `usrOffset` or other offset variables.                                                                                                       
                                Other atom types with similar last offset logic (beyond the user edit atom).                                                                                                  
                             - Any nested loops in slide show initialization or drawing record traversal that could fail to advance the input pointer.                                                           
                             - How the fuzzer harness feeds data into the POI parser and whether malformed input triggers pathological parsing paths.                                                            
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             This investigation should review every exit condition in the parsing loops and ensure that offsets always advance or that invalid offsets are handled by throwing                   
                             exceptions rather than looping indefinitely.                                                                                                                                        
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             ## Initial Issue Log                                                                                                                                                                
                             Here is the initial issue log of the codebase:                                                                                                                                      
                             <issue>                                                                                                                                                                             
                             ERROR: libFuzzer: timeout                                                                                                                                                           
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             </issue>                                                                                                                                                                            
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             ## Additional Issue Log

                             </additional_issue>                                                                                                                                                                 
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             ## Notes                                                                                                                                                                            
                             - All patch attempts are applied to the initial codebase. Reapply the the previous patches if needed.                                                                               
                             - If multiple different issues are present, all the issues must be resolved in a single patch attempt.                                                                              
                             - Try different approaches to resolve the issues.

                             <code>                                                                                                                                                                              
                             poi-scratchpad/src/main/java/org/apache/poi/hslf/usermodel/HSLFSlideShowImpl.java:251-286                                                                                           
                             ```                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             251:    private void buildRecords() throws IOException {                                                                                                                            
                             252:        // The format of records in a powerpoint file are:                                                                                                                      
                             253:        //   <little endian 2 byte "info">                                                                                                                                      
                             254:        //   <little endian 2 byte "type">                                                                                                                                      
                             255:        //   <little endian 4 byte "length">                                                                                                                                    
                             256:        // If it has a zero length, following it will be another record                                                                                                         
                             257:        //      <xx xx yy yy 00 00 00 00> <xx xx yy yy zz zz zz zz>                                                                                                             
                             258:        // If it has a length, depending on its type it may have children or data                                                                                               
                             259:        // If it has children, these will follow straight away                                                                                                                  
                             260:        //      <xx xx yy yy zz zz zz zz <xx xx yy yy zz zz zz zz>>                                                                                                             
                             261:        // If it has data, this will come straight after, and run for the length                                                                                                
                             262:        //      <xx xx yy yy zz zz zz zz dd dd dd dd dd dd dd>                                                                                                                  
                             263:        // All lengths given exclude the 8 byte record header                                                                                                                   
                             264:        // (Data records are known as Atoms)                                                                                                                                    
                             265:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             266:        // Document should start with:                                                                                                                                          
                             267:        //   0F 00 E8 03 ## ## ## ##                                                                                                                                            
                             268:        //     (type 1000 = document, info 00 0f is normal, rest is document length)                                                                                            
                             269:        //   01 00 E9 03 28 00 00 00                                                                                                                                            
                             270:        //     (type 1001 = document atom, info 00 01 normal, 28 bytes long)                                                                                                    
                             271:        //   80 16 00 00 E0 10 00 00 xx xx xx xx xx xx xx xx                                                                                                                    
                             272:        //   05 00 00 00 0A 00 00 00 xx xx xx                                                                                                                                   
                             273:        //     (the contents of the document atom, not sure what it means yet)                                                                                                  
                             274:        //   (records then follow)                                                                                                                                              
                             275:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             276:        // When parsing a document, look to see if you know about that type                                                                                                     
                             277:        //  of the current record. If you know it's a type that has children,                                                                                                   
                             278:        //  process the record's data area looking for more records                                                                                                             
                             279:        // If you know about the type and it doesn't have children, either do                                                                                                   
                             280:        //  something with the data (eg TextRun) or skip over it                                                                                                                
                             281:        // If you don't know about the type, play safe and skip over it (using                                                                                                  
                             282:        //  its length to know where the next record will start)                                                                                                                
                             283:        //                                                                                                                                                                      
                             284:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             285:        _records = read(_docstream, (int) currentUser.getCurrentEditOffset());                                                                                                  
                             286:    }                                                                                                                                                                           
                             ```                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             </code>

                             319:            Record builtRecord = Record.buildRecordAtOffset(docstream, usrOffset);

                             322:            }

                             330:                throw new CorruptPowerPointFileException("Powerpoint document is missing a PersistPtrHolder at " + psrOffset);                                                  
                             331:            }                                                                                                                                                                   
                             332:            if (!(record instanceof PersistPtrHolder)) {                                                                                                                        
                             333:                throw new CorruptPowerPointFileException("Record is not a PersistPtrHolder: " + record + " at " + psrOffset);                                                   
                             334:            }                                                                                                                                                                   
                             335:            PersistPtrHolder ptr = (PersistPtrHolder) record;                                                                                                                   
                             336:            recordMap.put(psrOffset, ptr);                                                                                                                                      
                             337:

                             339:                Integer offset = entry.getValue();

                             346:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             347:            // check for corrupted user edit atom and try to repair it                                                                                                          
                             348:            // if the next user edit atom offset is already known, we would go into an endless loop                                                                             
                             349:            if (usrOffset > 0 && recordMap.containsKey(usrOffset)) {

                             355:                int len = LittleEndian.getInt(docstream, usrOffset + 4);                                                                                                        
                             356:                if (ver_inst == 0 && type == 4085 && (len == 0x1C || len == 0x20)) {                                                                                            
                             357:                    LOG.atWarn().log("Repairing invalid user edit atom");                                                                                                       
                             358:                    usr.setLastUserEditAtomOffset(usrOffset);                                                                                                                   
                             359:                } else {                                                                                                                                                        
                             360:                    throw new CorruptPowerPointFileException("Powerpoint document contains invalid user edit atom");                                                            
                             361:                }                                                                                                                                                               
                             362:            }                                                                                                                                                                   
                             363:        }                                                                                                                                                                       
                             364:    }

                             <code>                                                                                                                                                                              
                             poi-scratchpad/src/main/java/org/apache/poi/hslf/usermodel/HSLFSlideShowImpl.java:251-286                                                                                           
                             ```                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             251:    private void buildRecords() throws IOException {                                                                                                                            
                             252:        // The format of records in a powerpoint file are:                                                                                                                      
                             253:        //   <little endian 2 byte "info">                                                                                                                                      
                             254:        //   <little endian 2 byte "type">                                                                                                                                      
                             255:        //   <little endian 4 byte "length">                                                                                                                                    
                             256:        // If it has a zero length, following it will be another record                                                                                                         
                             257:        //      <xx xx yy yy 00 00 00 00> <xx xx yy yy zz zz zz zz>                                                                                                             
                             258:        // If it has a length, depending on its type it may have children or data                                                                                               
                             259:        // If it has children, these will follow straight away                                                                                                                  
                             260:        //      <xx xx yy yy zz zz zz zz <xx xx yy yy zz zz zz zz>>                                                                                                             
                             261:        // If it has data, this will come straight after, and run for the length                                                                                                
                             262:        //      <xx xx yy yy zz zz zz zz dd dd dd dd dd dd dd>                                                                                                                  
                             263:        // All lengths given exclude the 8 byte record header                                                                                                                   
                             264:        // (Data records are known as Atoms)                                                                                                                                    
                             265:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             266:        // Document should start with:                                                                                                                                          
                             267:        //   0F 00 E8 03 ## ## ## ##                                                                                                                                            
                             268:        //     (type 1000 = document, info 00 0f is normal, rest is document length)                                                                                            
                             269:        //   01 00 E9 03 28 00 00 00                                                                                                                                            
                             270:        //     (type 1001 = document atom, info 00 01 normal, 28 bytes long)                                                                                                    
                             271:        //   80 16 00 00 E0 10 00 00 xx xx xx xx xx xx xx xx                                                                                                                    
                             272:        //   05 00 00 00 0A 00 00 00 xx xx xx                                                                                                                                   
                             273:        //     (the contents of the document atom, not sure what it means yet)                                                                                                  
                             274:        //   (records then follow)                                                                                                                                              
                             275:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             276:        // When parsing a document, look to see if you know about that type                                                                                                     
                             277:        //  of the current record. If you know it's a type that has children,                                                                                                   
                             278:        //  process the record's data area looking for more records                                                                                                             
                             279:        // If you know about the type and it doesn't have children, either do                                                                                                   
                             280:        //  something with the data (eg TextRun) or skip over it                                                                                                                
                             281:        // If you don't know about the type, play safe and skip over it (using                                                                                                  
                             282:        //  its length to know where the next record will start)                                                                                                                
                             283:        //                                                                                                                                                                      
                             284:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             285:        _records = read(_docstream, (int) currentUser.getCurrentEditOffset());                                                                                                  
                             286:    }                                                                                                                                                                           
                             ```                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             </code>                                                                                                                                                                             
                             <code>                                                                                                                                                                              
                             poi-scratchpad/src/main/java/org/apache/poi/hslf/usermodel/HSLFSlideShowImpl.java:288-315                                                                                           
                             ```                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             288:    private Record[] read(byte[] docstream, int usrOffset) throws IOException {                                                                                                 
                             289:        //sort found records by offset.                                                                                                                                         
                             290:        //(it is not necessary but SlideShow.findMostRecentCoreRecords() expects them sorted)                                                                                   
                             291:        NavigableMap<Integer, Record> records = new TreeMap<>(); // offset -> record                                                                                            
                             292:        Map<Integer, Integer> persistIds = new HashMap<>(); // offset -> persistId                                                                                              
                             293:        initRecordOffsets(docstream, usrOffset, records, persistIds);                                                                                                           
                             294:        HSLFSlideShowEncrypted decryptData = new HSLFSlideShowEncrypted(docstream, records);                                                                                    
                             295:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             296:        for (Map.Entry<Integer, Record> entry : records.entrySet()) {                                                                                                           
                             297:            Integer offset = entry.getKey();                                                                                                                                    
                             298:            Record record = entry.getValue();                                                                                                                                   
                             299:            Integer persistId = persistIds.get(offset);                                                                                                                         
                             300:            if (record == null) {                                                                                                                                               
                             301:                // all plain records have been already added,                                                                                                                   
                             302:                // only new records need to be decrypted (tbd #35897)                                                                                                           
                             303:                decryptData.decryptRecord(docstream, persistId, offset);                                                                                                        
                             304:                record = Record.buildRecordAtOffset(docstream, offset);                                                                                                         
                             305:                entry.setValue(record);                                                                                                                                         
                             306:            }                                                                                                                                                                   
                             307:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             308:            if (record instanceof PersistRecord) {                                                                                                                              
                             309:                ((PersistRecord) record).setPersistId(persistId);                                                                                                               
                             310:            }                                                                                                                                                                   
                             311:        }                                                                                                                                                                       
                             312:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             313:        decryptData.close();                                                                                                                                                    
                             314:        return records.values().toArray(new Record[0]);                                                                                                                         
                             315:    }                                                                                                                                                                           
                             ```                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             </code>                                                                                                                                                                             
                             <code>                                                                                                                                                                              
                             poi-scratchpad/src/main/java/org/apache/poi/hslf/usermodel/HSLFSlideShowImpl.java:317-364                                                                                           
                             ```                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             317:    private void initRecordOffsets(byte[] docstream, int usrOffset, NavigableMap<Integer, Record> recordMap, Map<Integer, Integer> offset2id) {                                 
                             318:        while (usrOffset != 0) {                                                                                                                                                
                             319:            Record builtRecord = Record.buildRecordAtOffset(docstream, usrOffset);                                                                                              
                             320:            if (!(builtRecord instanceof UserEditAtom)) {                                                                                                                       
                             321:                throw new CorruptPowerPointFileException("Did not have a user edit atom: " + builtRecord);                                                                      
                             322:            }                                                                                                                                                                   
                             323:            UserEditAtom usr = (UserEditAtom) builtRecord;                                                                                                                      
                             324:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             325:            recordMap.put(usrOffset, usr);                                                                                                                                      
                             326:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             327:            int psrOffset = usr.getPersistPointersOffset();                                                                                                                     
                             328:            Record record = Record.buildRecordAtOffset(docstream, psrOffset);                                                                                                   
                             329:            if (record == null) {                                                                                                                                               
                             330:                throw new CorruptPowerPointFileException("Powerpoint document is missing a PersistPtrHolder at " + psrOffset);                                                  
                             331:            }                                                                                                                                                                   
                             332:            if (!(record instanceof PersistPtrHolder)) {                                                                                                                        
                             333:                throw new CorruptPowerPointFileException("Record is not a PersistPtrHolder: " + record + " at " + psrOffset);                                                   
                             334:            }                                                                                                                                                                   
                             335:            PersistPtrHolder ptr = (PersistPtrHolder) record;                                                                                                                   
                             336:            recordMap.put(psrOffset, ptr);                                                                                                                                      
                             337:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             338:            for (Map.Entry<Integer, Integer> entry : ptr.getSlideLocationsLookup().entrySet()) {                                                                                
                             339:                Integer offset = entry.getValue();                                                                                                                              
                             340:                Integer id = entry.getKey();                                                                                                                                    
                             341:                recordMap.put(offset, null); // reserve a slot for the record                                                                                                   
                             342:                offset2id.put(offset, id);                                                                                                                                      
                             343:            }                                                                                                                                                                   
                             344:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             345:            usrOffset = usr.getLastUserEditAtomOffset();                                                                                                                        
                             346:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             347:            // check for corrupted user edit atom and try to repair it                                                                                                          
                             348:            // if the next user edit atom offset is already known, we would go into an endless loop                                                                             
                             349:            if (usrOffset > 0 && recordMap.containsKey(usrOffset)) {                                                                                                            
                             350:                // a user edit atom is usually located 36 byte before the smallest known record offset                                                                          
                             351:                usrOffset = recordMap.firstKey() - 36;                                                                                                                          
                             352:                // check that we really are located on a user edit atom                                                                                                         
                             353:                int ver_inst = LittleEndian.getUShort(docstream, usrOffset);                                                                                                    
                             354:                int type = LittleEndian.getUShort(docstream, usrOffset + 2);                                                                                                    
                             355:                int len = LittleEndian.getInt(docstream, usrOffset + 4);                                                                                                        
                             356:                if (ver_inst == 0 && type == 4085 && (len == 0x1C || len == 0x20)) {                                                                                            
                             357:                    LOG.atWarn().log("Repairing invalid user edit atom");                                                                                                       
                             358:                    usr.setLastUserEditAtomOffset(usrOffset);                                                                                                                   
                             359:                } else {                                                                                                                                                        
                             360:                    throw new CorruptPowerPointFileException("Powerpoint document contains invalid user edit atom");                                                            
                             361:                }                                                                                                                                                               
                             362:            }                                                                                                                                                                   
                             363:        }                                                                                                                                                                       
                             364:    }                                                                                                                                                                           
                             ```                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             </code>

                             339:                Integer offset = entry.getValue();

                             341:                recordMap.put(offset, null); // reserve a slot for the record                                                                                                   
                             342:                offset2id.put(offset, id);                                                                                                                                      
                             343:            }                                                                                                                                                                   
                             344:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             345:            usrOffset = usr.getLastUserEditAtomOffset();                                                                                                                        
                             346:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             347:            // check for corrupted user edit atom and try to repair it                                                                                                          
                             348:            // if the next user edit atom offset is already known, we would go into an endless loop                                                                             
                             349:            if (usrOffset > 0 && recordMap.containsKey(usrOffset)) {                                                                                                            
                             350:                // a user edit atom is usually located 36 byte before the smallest known record offset                                                                          
                             351:                usrOffset = recordMap.firstKey() - 36;

                             353:                int ver_inst = LittleEndian.getUShort(docstream, usrOffset);                                                                                                    
                             354:                int type = LittleEndian.getUShort(docstream, usrOffset + 2);                                                                                                    
                             355:                int len = LittleEndian.getInt(docstream, usrOffset + 4);                                                                                                        
                             356:                if (ver_inst == 0 && type == 4085 && (len == 0x1C || len == 0x20)) {                                                                                            
                             357:                    LOG.atWarn().log("Repairing invalid user edit atom");                                                                                                       
                             358:                    usr.setLastUserEditAtomOffset(usrOffset);                                                                                                                   
                             359:                } else {                                                                                                                                                        
                             360:                    throw new CorruptPowerPointFileException("Powerpoint document contains invalid user edit atom");                                                            
                             361:                }                                                                                                                                                               
                             362:            }                                                                                                                                                                   
                             363:        }

                             </code_snippets>                                                                                                                                                                    
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             ## Fix Strategy                                                                                                                                                                     
                             <fix_strategy>                                                                                                                                                                      
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             1. Reinstate and enhance loop-termination guards in initRecordOffsets:                                                                                                              
                                a. Introduce a `Set<Integer> seenUsrOffsets` at method start to track all `usrOffset` values encountered.                                                                        
                                b. On each loop iteration, before building the record, check if `usrOffset` is already in `seenUsrOffsets`. If so, throw a `CorruptPowerPointFileException`                      
                             indicating a cyclic or repeated user-edit chain.                                                                                                                                    
                                c. This replaces the previous break on recordMap.containsKey repair logic, ensuring that malformed inputs do not hang but fail fast.                                           
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             2. Validate bounds of every computed offset:                                                                                                                                        
                                a. After computing the next `usrOffset` (either via `usr.getLastUserEditAtomOffset()` or the old repair formula), verify that `usrOffset >= 0` and `usrOffset                  
                             + 8 <= docstream.length`. If out of bounds, throw `CorruptPowerPointFileException`.                                                                                                 
                                b. This prevents attempts to read headers at invalid positions and avoids silent infinite loops when offsets wander off into garbage.                                            
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             3. Remove the existing break branch on repeated offsets:                                                                                                                          
                                a. The prior patchs `if (recordMap.containsKey(usrOffset)) { LOG; break; }` should be eliminated in favor of the new cycle-detection and immediate exception.                  
                                b. This simplification ensures that no pathological inputs slip past the break into the outer parsing, possibly leading to other loops.                                          
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             4. Preserve existing happy-path logic:                                                                                                                                              
                                a. All original calls to `Record.buildRecordAtOffset`, `PersistPtrHolder` processing, and map population remain unchanged.                                                       
                                b. Only the pre-check for seen offsets and bounds checks are added, so well-formed documents parse identically.                                                                  
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             5. Apply changes directly to `HSLFSlideShowImpl.initRecordOffsets` in `poi-scratchpad/src/main/java/org/apache/poi/hslf/usermodel/HSLFSlideShowImpl.java`, lines                    
                             ~317364.                                                                                                                                                                           
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             Justification:                                                                                                                                                                      
                             - By tracking seen offsets, we guarantee loop termination on cyclic or repeating chains rather than hanging indefinitely, satisfying the fuzzers timeliness                        
                             requirement.                                                                                                                                                                        
                             - Bounds validation prevents invalid memory reads and stops spurious offset growth.                                                                                                 
                             - Throwing `CorruptPowerPointFileException` is consistent with existing error-handling on malformed streams.                                                                        
                             - No harness or test code is modified; existing behavior on valid inputs remains intact.                                                                                            
                             - Similar cycle-guards are used elsewhere in Apache POI (e.g., when parsing property sets or container hierarchies), demonstrating precedent for this approach.                     
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             Potential Side Effects & Mitigations:                                                                                                                                               
                             - Well-formed files never revisit the same user-edit offset, so no existing behavior is changed.                                                                                    
                             - Malformed inputs now produce a controlled exception instead of a hang; if consumers expect silent skips, they should catch `CorruptPowerPointFileException`.                      
                             - Fuzzer runs will now detect parsing failures rather than timeouts, enabling new crash/exception coverage without modifying harness logic.                                         
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             File paths to patch (example context):                                                                                                                                              
                             <code_range>poi-scratchpad/src/main/java/org/apache/poi/hslf/usermodel/HSLFSlideShowImpl.java:317-364</code_range>                                                                  
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             </fix_strategy>                                                                                                                                                                     
                             ===Evaluation End===

                                      while (usrOffset != 0) {
