                             ERROR: libFuzzer: timeout                                                                                                                                                           
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             ===Issue===                                                                                                                                                                         
                             ERROR: libFuzzer: timeout                                                                                                                                                           
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             ===Evaluation Report===                                                                                                                                                             
                             # Evaluation Report                                                                                                                                                                 
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             ## Summary                                                                                                                                                                          
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             The initial issue reported by the libFuzzer harness was a timeout (hang) when exercising the HSLFSlideShowImpl code in Apache POI. A patch was proposed to guard                    
                             against infinite loops in the `initRecordOffsets` method by:                                                                                                                        
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             - Introducing a `Set<Integer> seenUsrOffsets` to detect and break cyclic useredit chains.                                                                                          
                             - Adding bounds checks on the next useredit atom offset to prevent overruns or invalid offsets.                                                                                    
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             After applying the patch, the fuzzer still reports the same timeout error, indicating the hang condition remains.                                                                   
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             ## Description                                                                                                                                                                      
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             1. Initial Issue                                                                                                                                                                    
                                The libFuzzer log simply reports:                                                                                                                                                
                                  ERROR: libFuzzer: timeout                                                                                                                                                      
                                This indicates that the fuzzer encountered an input which caused the code under test to hang or loop indefinitely, exceeding the allotted execution time limit.                  
                             No stack trace or exception was produced, suggesting the code entered a long or infinite loop.                                                                                      
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             2. Important Observations                                                                                                                                                           
                                - The hang happens inside the `HSLFSlideShowImpl` class, specifically in the `initRecordOffsets` method.                                                                         
                                - The original implementation walks a chain of user edit atom records by repeatedly calling `usr.getLastUserEditAtomOffset()` and updating `usrOffset`.                        
                                - There was no protection against:                                                                                                                                               
                                   Cycles in the chain of offsets                                                                                                                                               
                                   Invalid or outofbounds offsets                                                                                                                                             
                                - Without these guards, a malformed PPT stream can lead the loop to spin indefinitely.                                                                                           
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             3. Patch Attempt                                                                                                                                                                    
                                The submitted patch makes two main changes in `HSLFSlideShowImpl.java`:                                                                                                          
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                                a) Cycle detection:                                                                                                                                                              
                                ```diff                                                                                                                                                                          
                                 private void initRecordOffsets(byte[] docstream, int usrOffset,                                                                                                                 
                                         NavigableMap<Integer, Record> recordMap, Map<Integer, Integer> offset2id) {                                                                                             
                             +       // track seen user edit atom offsets to detect cycles                                                                                                                       
                             +       Set<Integer> seenUsrOffsets = new HashSet<>();                                                                                                                              
                                     while (usrOffset != 0) {                                                                                                                                                    
                             +           if (!seenUsrOffsets.add(usrOffset)) {                                                                                                                                   
                             +               throw new CorruptPowerPointFileException(                                                                                                                           
                             +                   "Cyclic user edit chain detected at offset " + usrOffset);                                                                                                      
                             +           }                                                                                                                                                                       
                                         Record builtRecord = Record.buildRecordAtOffset(docstream, usrOffset);                                                                                                  
                                         if (!(builtRecord instanceof UserEditAtom)) {                                                                                                                           
                                             throw new CorruptPowerPointFileException(                                                                                                                           
                                                 "Did not have a user edit atom: " + builtRecord);                                                                                                               
                                         }                                                                                                                                                                       
                                ```                                                                                                                                                                              
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                                b) Bounds validation on the next offset:                                                                                                                                         
                                ```diff                                                                                                                                                                          
                                         usrOffset = usr.getLastUserEditAtomOffset();                                                                                                                            
                             +           // validate usrOffset bounds to prevent infinite loop or buffer overrun                                                                                                 
                             +           if (usrOffset < 0 || usrOffset + 8 > docstream.length) {                                                                                                                
                             +               throw new CorruptPowerPointFileException(                                                                                                                           
                             +                   "Invalid user edit atom offset out of bounds: " + usrOffset);                                                                                                   
                             +           }                                                                                                                                                                       
                                ```                                                                                                                                                                              
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                                These changes were applied around lines 315350 of `HSLFSlideShowImpl.java`, adjusting imports to include `Set` and `HashSet`.                                                   
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             4. PostPatch Result                                                                                                                                                                
                                After recompiling with the patch in place, running the same libFuzzer harness input still produces:                                                                              
                                  ERROR: libFuzzer: timeout                                                                                                                                                      
                                This confirms that although cycle detection and bounds checks were added, the underlying hang remains unaddressed.                                                               
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             5. Areas for Further Investigation                                                                                                                                                  
                                To fully understand and resolve the timeout, the following code regions should be reviewed:                                                                                      
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                                - The full code path within `initRecordOffsets`, including:                                                                                                                      
                                   How `Record.buildRecordAtOffset` advances through the document stream                                                                                                        
                                   The logic of `UserEditAtom.getLastUserEditAtomOffset()` and whether it ever returns 0 to terminate                                                                           
                                - Any other loops or recursive traversals in the HSLF module that process record chains or trees                                                                                 
                                - Interaction between `offset2id` map and cycle detection in other parts of the slideshow initialization                                                                         
                                - Edge conditions in record parsing (length fields, header offsets) that could trigger long loops without jumping back to offset 0                                               
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             Investigating these areas will give a more holistic view of where the slideshow parsing logic may hang on malformed or adversarial inputs, beyond just the                          
                             useredit atom chain.

                             317:    private void initRecordOffsets(byte[] docstream, int usrOffset, NavigableMap<Integer, Record> recordMap, Map<Integer, Integer> offset2id) {                                 
                             318:        while (usrOffset != 0) {                                                                                                                                                
                             319:            Record builtRecord = Record.buildRecordAtOffset(docstream, usrOffset);                                                                                              
                             320:            if (!(builtRecord instanceof UserEditAtom)) {                                                                                                                       
                             321:                throw new CorruptPowerPointFileException("Did not have a user edit atom: " + builtRecord);                                                                      
                             322:            }                                                                                                                                                                   
                             323:            UserEditAtom usr = (UserEditAtom) builtRecord;                                                                                                                      
                             324:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             325:            recordMap.put(usrOffset, usr);                                                                                                                                      
                             326:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             327:            int psrOffset = usr.getPersistPointersOffset();                                                                                                                     
                             328:            Record record = Record.buildRecordAtOffset(docstream, psrOffset);                                                                                                   
                             329:            if (record == null) {                                                                                                                                               
                             330:                throw new CorruptPowerPointFileException("Powerpoint document is missing a PersistPtrHolder at " + psrOffset);                                                  
                             331:            }                                                                                                                                                                   
                             332:            if (!(record instanceof PersistPtrHolder)) {                                                                                                                        
                             333:                throw new CorruptPowerPointFileException("Record is not a PersistPtrHolder: " + record + " at " + psrOffset);                                                   
                             334:            }                                                                                                                                                                   
                             335:            PersistPtrHolder ptr = (PersistPtrHolder) record;                                                                                                                   
                             336:            recordMap.put(psrOffset, ptr);                                                                                                                                      
                             337:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             338:            for (Map.Entry<Integer, Integer> entry : ptr.getSlideLocationsLookup().entrySet()) {                                                                                
                             339:                Integer offset = entry.getValue();                                                                                                                              
                             340:                Integer id = entry.getKey();                                                                                                                                    
                             341:                recordMap.put(offset, null); // reserve a slot for the record                                                                                                   
                             342:                offset2id.put(offset, id);                                                                                                                                      
                             343:            }                                                                                                                                                                   
                             344:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             345:            usrOffset = usr.getLastUserEditAtomOffset();                                                                                                                        
                             346:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             347:            // check for corrupted user edit atom and try to repair it                                                                                                          
                             348:            // if the next user edit atom offset is already known, we would go into an endless loop                                                                             
                             349:            if (usrOffset > 0 && recordMap.containsKey(usrOffset)) {                                                                                                            
                             350:                // a user edit atom is usually located 36 byte before the smallest known record offset                                                                          
                             351:                usrOffset = recordMap.firstKey() - 36;                                                                                                                          
                             352:                // check that we really are located on a user edit atom                                                                                                         
                             353:                int ver_inst = LittleEndian.getUShort(docstream, usrOffset);                                                                                                    
                             354:                int type = LittleEndian.getUShort(docstream, usrOffset + 2);                                                                                                    
                             355:                int len = LittleEndian.getInt(docstream, usrOffset + 4);                                                                                                        
                             356:                if (ver_inst == 0 && type == 4085 && (len == 0x1C || len == 0x20)) {                                                                                            
                             357:                    LOG.atWarn().log("Repairing invalid user edit atom");                                                                                                       
                             358:                    usr.setLastUserEditAtomOffset(usrOffset);                                                                                                                   
                             359:                } else {                                                                                                                                                        
                             360:                    throw new CorruptPowerPointFileException("Powerpoint document contains invalid user edit atom");                                                            
                             361:                }                                                                                                                                                               
                             362:            }

                             ===Patch Result===                                                                                                                                                                  
                             ERROR: libFuzzer: timeout                                                                                                                                                           
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             ===Issue===                                                                                                                                                                         
                             ERROR: libFuzzer: timeout                                                                                                                                                           
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             ===Evaluation Report===                                                                                                                                                             
                             # Evaluation Report                                                                                                                                                                 
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             ## Summary                                                                                                                                                                          
                             The initial issue reported by libFuzzer was a timeout, indicating that the fuzzing run hung or took too long on a particular input. A patch was applied to the                      
                             `initRecordOffsets` method in `HSLFSlideShowImpl.java` that introduced:                                                                                                             
                             - Cycle detection using a `Set<Integer>` to track seen offsets.                                                                                                                     
                             - A maximum iteration count based on the document stream length.                                                                                                                    
                             - Bounds checking on the next offset.                                                                                                                                               
                             These checks throw `CorruptPowerPointFileException` on detection of cycles, excessive iterations, or out-of-bounds offsets. After applying the patch, libFuzzer                     
                             still reports the same timeout error.                                                                                                                                               
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             ## Description                                                                                                                                                                      
                             1. Initial issue                                                                                                                                                                    
                                - The fuzzer harness invoked the PowerPoint parsing code and ultimately hung, resulting in                                                                                       
                                  `ERROR: libFuzzer: timeout`.                                                                                                                                                   
                                - No stack trace or exception was raised; the process simply exceeded the allowed execution time.                                                                                
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             2. Observations from the initial issue                                                                                                                                              
                                - The timeout suggests an infinite loop or extremely long loop in the parsing logic.                                                                                             
                                - The prime suspect for looping is the `while (usrOffset != 0)` loop in `initRecordOffsets`, which walks a chain of user edit atoms.                                             
                                - No bounds checks or cycle prevention measures existed before the patch, so a malformed chain could easily loop indefinitely.                                                   
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             3. Patch attempt details                                                                                                                                                            
                                - Imports added at the top of `HSLFSlideShowImpl.java`:                                                                                                                          
                                  ```java                                                                                                                                                                        
                                  import java.util.Set;                                                                                                                                                          
                                  import java.util.HashSet;                                                                                                                                                      
                                  ```                                                                                                                                                                            
                                - In `initRecordOffsets(byte[] docstream, int usrOffset, NavigableMap<Integer, Record> recordMap, Map<Integer, Integer> offset2id)`:                                             
                                  ```diff                                                                                                                                                                        
                                  +    Set<Integer> seenUsrOffsets = new HashSet<>();                                                                                                                            
                                  +    int iterationCount = 0;                                                                                                                                                   
                                  +    int maxIterations = docstream.length > 0 ? docstream.length : 1000;                                                                                                       
                                       while (usrOffset != 0) {                                                                                                                                                  
                                  +        if (iterationCount++ > maxIterations) {                                                                                                                               
                                  +            throw new CorruptPowerPointFileException(                                                                                                                         
                                  +                "Too many user edit atom iterations: " + iterationCount);                                                                                                     
                                  +        }                                                                                                                                                                     
                                  +        if (!seenUsrOffsets.add(usrOffset)) {                                                                                                                                 
                                  +            throw new CorruptPowerPointFileException(                                                                                                                         
                                  +                "Cyclic user edit chain detected at offset " + usrOffset);                                                                                                    
                                  +        }                                                                                                                                                                     
                                        Record builtRecord = Record.buildRecordAtOffset(docstream, usrOffset);                                                                                                   
                                        if (!(builtRecord instanceof UserEditAtom)) {                                                                                                                            
                                            throw new CorruptPowerPointFileException("Did not have a user edit atom: " + builtRecord);                                                                           
                                        }                                                                                                                                                                        
                                  @@ -343,6 +356,11 @@                                                                                                                                                           
                                        usrOffset = usr.getLastUserEditAtomOffset();                                                                                                                             
                                  +      if (usrOffset < 0 || usrOffset + 8 > docstream.length) {                                                                                                                
                                  +          throw new CorruptPowerPointFileException(                                                                                                                           
                                  +              "Invalid user edit atom offset out of bounds: " + usrOffset);                                                                                                   
                                  +      }                                                                                                                                                                       
                                  ```                                                                                                                                                                            
                                - After recompiling with these changes, libFuzzer still reports `ERROR: libFuzzer: timeout`.                                                                                     
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             4. Post-patch log                                                                                                                                                                   
                                - No new exceptions were thrown; the timeout persisted.                                                                                                                          
                                - This implies that either the new checks are never triggered on the problematic input, or another loop elsewhere is responsible for the hang.                                   
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             5. Areas for further investigation                                                                                                                                                  
                                - The `initRecordOffsets` method loop structure, including:                                                                                                                      
                                   How `Record.buildRecordAtOffset` determines the next offset.                                                                                                                 
                                   Whether other record types or malformed data bypass the new checks.                                                                                                          
                                - Other potential loops in the PPT parsing code (e.g., nested record visitors or recursive parsing of shape/group records).                                                      
                                - The fuzzer harness entry point to confirm which code paths it exercises and whether it can drive the new exception conditions.                                                 
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             ## Initial Issue Log                                                                                                                                                                
                             Here is the initial issue log of the codebase:                                                                                                                                      
                             <issue>                                                                                                                                                                             
                             ERROR: libFuzzer: timeout                                                                                                                                                           
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             </issue>                                                                                                                                                                            
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             ## Additional Issue Log                                                                                                                                                             
                             Here is the additional issue log after the last patch attempt:                                                                                                                      
                             <additional_issue>

                             ## Notes                                                                                                                                                                            
                             - All patch attempts are applied to the initial codebase. Reapply the the previous patches if needed.                                                                               
                             - If multiple different issues are present, all the issues must be resolved in a single patch attempt.                                                                              
                             - Try different approaches to resolve the issues.

                             325:            recordMap.put(usrOffset, usr);                                                                                                                                      
                             326:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             327:            int psrOffset = usr.getPersistPointersOffset();                                                                                                                     
                             328:            Record record = Record.buildRecordAtOffset(docstream, psrOffset);                                                                                                   
                             329:            if (record == null) {                                                                                                                                               
                             330:                throw new CorruptPowerPointFileException("Powerpoint document is missing a PersistPtrHolder at " + psrOffset);                                                  
                             331:            }                                                                                                                                                                   
                             332:            if (!(record instanceof PersistPtrHolder)) {                                                                                                                        
                             333:                throw new CorruptPowerPointFileException("Record is not a PersistPtrHolder: " + record + " at " + psrOffset);                                                   
                             334:            }                                                                                                                                                                   
                             335:            PersistPtrHolder ptr = (PersistPtrHolder) record;                                                                                                                   
                             336:            recordMap.put(psrOffset, ptr);                                                                                                                                      
                             337:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             338:            for (Map.Entry<Integer, Integer> entry : ptr.getSlideLocationsLookup().entrySet()) {                                                                                
                             339:                Integer offset = entry.getValue();                                                                                                                              
                             340:                Integer id = entry.getKey();                                                                                                                                    
                             341:                recordMap.put(offset, null); // reserve a slot for the record                                                                                                   
                             342:                offset2id.put(offset, id);                                                                                                                                      
                             343:            }                                                                                                                                                                   
                             344:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             345:            usrOffset = usr.getLastUserEditAtomOffset();                                                                                                                        
                             346:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             347:            // check for corrupted user edit atom and try to repair it                                                                                                          
                             348:            // if the next user edit atom offset is already known, we would go into an endless loop                                                                             
                             349:            if (usrOffset > 0 && recordMap.containsKey(usrOffset)) {                                                                                                            
                             350:                // a user edit atom is usually located 36 byte before the smallest known record offset                                                                          
                             351:                usrOffset = recordMap.firstKey() - 36;                                                                                                                          
                             352:                // check that we really are located on a user edit atom                                                                                                         
                             353:                int ver_inst = LittleEndian.getUShort(docstream, usrOffset);                                                                                                    
                             354:                int type = LittleEndian.getUShort(docstream, usrOffset + 2);                                                                                                    
                             355:                int len = LittleEndian.getInt(docstream, usrOffset + 4);                                                                                                        
                             356:                if (ver_inst == 0 && type == 4085 && (len == 0x1C || len == 0x20)) {                                                                                            
                             357:                    LOG.atWarn().log("Repairing invalid user edit atom");                                                                                                       
                             358:                    usr.setLastUserEditAtomOffset(usrOffset);                                                                                                                   
                             359:                } else {                                                                                                                                                        
                             360:                    throw new CorruptPowerPointFileException("Powerpoint document contains invalid user edit atom");                                                            
                             361:                }                                                                                                                                                               
                             362:            }                                                                                                                                                                   
                             363:        }                                                                                                                                                                       
                             364:    }                                                                                                                                                                           
                             ```                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             </code>

                             1:/* ====================================================================
