                             18:package org.apache.poi.hslf.record;                                                                                                                                              
                             19:                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             20:import java.io.IOException;                                                                                                                                                      
                             21:import java.io.OutputStream;                                                                                                                                                     
                             22:import java.util.ArrayList;                                                                                                                                                      
                             23:import java.util.Arrays;                                                                                                                                                         
                             24:import java.util.List;                                                                                                                                                           
                             25:                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             26:import org.apache.logging.log4j.Logger;                                                                                                                                          
                             27:import org.apache.poi.logging.PoiLogManager;                                                                                                                                     
                             28:import org.apache.logging.log4j.message.StringFormattedMessage;                                                                                                                  
                             29:import org.apache.poi.common.usermodel.GenericRecord;                                                                                                                            
                             30:import org.apache.poi.hslf.exceptions.CorruptPowerPointFileException;                                                                                                            
                             31:import org.apache.poi.hslf.exceptions.HSLFException;                                                                                                                             
                             32:import org.apache.poi.hslf.record.RecordTypes.RecordConstructor;                                                                                                                 
                             33:import org.apache.poi.util.LittleEndian;                                                                                                                                         
                             34:                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             35:import static org.apache.logging.log4j.util.Unbox.box;                                                                                                                           
                             36:                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             37:/**                                                                                                                                                                              
                             38: * This abstract class represents a record in the PowerPoint document.                                                                                                           
                             39: * Record classes should extend with RecordContainer or RecordAtom, which                                                                                                        
                             40: *  extend this in turn.                                                                                                                                                         
                             41: */                                                                                                                                                                              
                             42:                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             43:public abstract class Record implements GenericRecord                                                                                                                            
                             44:{                                                                                                                                                                                
                             45:    // For logging                                                                                                                                                               
                             46:    protected static final Logger LOG = PoiLogManager.getLogger(Record.class);                                                                                                   
                             47:                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             48:    /**                                                                                                                                                                          
                             49:     * Is this record type an Atom record (only has data),                                                                                                                       
                             50:     *  or is it a non-Atom record (has other records)?                                                                                                                          
                             51:     */                                                                                                                                                                          
                             52:    public abstract boolean isAnAtom();                                                                                                                                          
                             53:                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             54:    /**                                                                                                                                                                          
                             55:     * Returns the type (held as a little endian in bytes 3 and 4)                                                                                                               
                             56:     *  that this class handles                                                                                                                                                  
                             57:     */                                                                                                                                                                          
                             58:    public abstract long getRecordType();                                                                                                                                        
                             59:                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             60:    /**                                                                                                                                                                          
                             61:     * Fetch all the child records of this record                                                                                                                                
                             62:     * If this record is an atom, will return null                                                                                                                               
                             63:     * If this record is a non-atom, but has no children, will return                                                                                                            
                             64:     *  an empty array                                                                                                                                                           
                             65:     */                                                                                                                                                                          
                             66:    public abstract Record[] getChildRecords();                                                                                                                                  
                             67:                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             68:    /**                                                                                                                                                                          
                             69:     * Have the contents printer out into an OutputStream, used when                                                                                                             
                             70:     *  writing a file back out to disk                                                                                                                                          
                             71:     * (Normally, atom classes will keep their bytes around, but                                                                                                                 
                             72:     *  non atom classes will just request the bytes from their                                                                                                                  
                             73:     *  children, then chuck on their header and return)                                                                                                                         
                             74:     */                                                                                                                                                                          
                             75:    public abstract void writeOut(OutputStream o) throws IOException;                                                                                                            
                             76:                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             77:    @Override                                                                                                                                                                    
                             78:    public Enum getGenericRecordType() {                                                                                                                                         
                             79:        return RecordTypes.forTypeID((int)getRecordType());                                                                                                                      
                             80:    }                                                                                                                                                                            
                             81:                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             82:    @Override                                                                                                                                                                    
                             83:    public List<Record> getGenericChildren() {                                                                                                                                   
                             84:        Record[] recs = getChildRecords();                                                                                                                                       
                             85:        return (recs == null) ? null : Arrays.asList(recs);                                                                                                                      
                             86:    }                                                                                                                                                                            
                             87:                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             88:    /**                                                                                                                                                                          
                             89:     * When writing out, write out a signed int (32bit) in Little Endian format                                                                                                  
                             90:     */                                                                                                                                                                          
                             91:    public static void writeLittleEndian(int i,OutputStream o) throws IOException {                                                                                              
                             92:        byte[] bi = new byte[4];                                                                                                                                                 
                             93:        LittleEndian.putInt(bi,0,i);                                                                                                                                             
                             94:        o.write(bi);                                                                                                                                                             
                             95:    }                                                                                                                                                                            
                             96:    /**                                                                                                                                                                          
                             97:     * When writing out, write out a signed short (16bit) in Little Endian format                                                                                                
                             98:     */                                                                                                                                                                          
                             99:    public static void writeLittleEndian(short s,OutputStream o) throws IOException {                                                                                            
                             100:        byte[] bs = new byte[2];                                                                                                                                                
                             101:        LittleEndian.putShort(bs,0,s);                                                                                                                                          
                             102:        o.write(bs);                                                                                                                                                            
                             103:    }                                                                                                                                                                           
                             104:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             105:    /**                                                                                                                                                                         
                             106:     * Build and return the Record at the given offset.                                                                                                                         
                             107:     * Note - does less error checking and handling than findChildRecords                                                                                                       
                             108:     * @param b The byte array to build from                                                                                                                                    
                             109:     * @param offset The offset to build at                                                                                                                                     
                             110:     */                                                                                                                                                                         
                             111:    public static Record buildRecordAtOffset(byte[] b, int offset) {                                                                                                            
                             112:        long type = LittleEndian.getUShort(b,offset+2);                                                                                                                         
                             113:        long rlen = LittleEndian.getUInt(b,offset+4);                                                                                                                           
                             114:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             115:        // Sanity check the length                                                                                                                                              
                             116:        int rleni = (int)rlen;                                                                                                                                                  
                             117:        if(rleni < 0) { rleni = 0; }                                                                                                                                            
                             118:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             119:        return createRecordForType(type,b,offset,8+rleni);                                                                                                                      
                             120:    }                                                                                                                                                                           
                             121:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             122:    /**                                                                                                                                                                         
                             123:     * Default method for finding child records of a container record                                                                                                           
                             124:     */                                                                                                                                                                         
                             125:    public static Record[] findChildRecords(byte[] b, int start, int len) {                                                                                                     
                             126:        List<Record> children = new ArrayList<>(5);                                                                                                                             
                             127:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             128:        // Jump our little way along, creating records as we go                                                                                                                 
                             129:        int pos = start;                                                                                                                                                        
                             130:        while(pos <= (start+len-8)) {                                                                                                                                           
                             131:            long type = LittleEndian.getUShort(b,pos+2);                                                                                                                        
                             132:            long rlen = LittleEndian.getUInt(b,pos+4);                                                                                                                          
                             133:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             134:            // Sanity check the length                                                                                                                                          
                             135:            int rleni = (int)rlen;                                                                                                                                              
                             136:            if(rleni < 0) { rleni = 0; }                                                                                                                                        
                             137:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             138:            // Abort if first record is of type 0000 and length FFFF,                                                                                                           
                             139:            //  as that's a sign of a screwed up record                                                                                                                         
                             140:            if(pos == 0 && type == 0L && rleni == 0xffff) {                                                                                                                     
                             141:                throw new CorruptPowerPointFileException("Corrupt document - starts with record of type 0000 and length 0xFFFF");                                               
                             142:            }                                                                                                                                                                   
                             143:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             144:            Record r = createRecordForType(type,b,pos,8+rleni);                                                                                                                 
                             145:            if(r != null) {                                                                                                                                                     
                             146:                children.add(r);                                                                                                                                                
                             147:            }                                                                                                                                                                   
                             148:            pos += 8;                                                                                                                                                           
                             149:            pos += rleni;                                                                                                                                                       
                             150:        }                                                                                                                                                                       
                             151:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             152:        // Turn the vector into an array, and return                                                                                                                            
                             153:        return children.toArray(new Record[0]);                                                                                                                                 
                             154:    }                                                                                                                                                                           
                             155:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             156:    /**                                                                                                                                                                         
                             157:     * For a given type (little endian bytes 3 and 4 in record header),                                                                                                         
                             158:     *  byte array, start position and length:                                                                                                                                  
                             159:     *  will return a Record object that will handle that record                                                                                                                
                             160:     *                                                                                                                                                                          
                             161:     * Remember that while PPT stores the record lengths as 8 bytes short                                                                                                       
                             162:     *  (not including the size of the header), this code assumes you're                                                                                                        
                             163:     *  passing in corrected lengths                                                                                                                                            
                             164:     */                                                                                                                                                                         
                             165:    public static Record createRecordForType(long type, byte[] b, int start, int len) {                                                                                         
                             166:        // We use the RecordTypes class to provide us with the right                                                                                                            
                             167:        //  class to use for a given type                                                                                                                                       
                             168:        // A spot of reflection gets us the (byte[],int,int) constructor                                                                                                        
                             169:        // From there, we instantiate the class                                                                                                                                 
                             170:        // Any special record handling occurs once we have the class                                                                                                            
                             171:        RecordTypes recordType = RecordTypes.forTypeID((short) type);                                                                                                           
                             172:        RecordConstructor<?> c = recordType.recordConstructor;                                                                                                                  
                             173:        if (c == null) {                                                                                                                                                        
                             174:            // How odd. RecordTypes normally substitutes in                                                                                                                     
                             175:            //  a default handler class if it has heard of the record                                                                                                           
                             176:            //  type but there's no support for it. Explicitly request                                                                                                          
                             177:            //  that now                                                                                                                                                        
                             178:            LOG.atDebug().log(() -> new StringFormattedMessage("Known but unhandled record type %d (0x%04x) at offset %d", type, type, start));                                 
                             179:            c = RecordTypes.UnknownRecordPlaceholder.recordConstructor;                                                                                                         
                             180:        } else if (recordType == RecordTypes.UnknownRecordPlaceholder) {                                                                                                        
                             181:            LOG.atDebug().log(() -> new StringFormattedMessage("Unknown placeholder type %d (0x%04x) at offset %d", type, type, start));                                        
                             182:        }                                                                                                                                                                       
                             183:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             184:        final Record toReturn;                                                                                                                                                  
                             185:        try {                                                                                                                                                                   
                             186:            toReturn = c.apply(b, start, len);                                                                                                                                  
                             187:        } catch(RuntimeException e) {                                                                                                                                           
                             188:            // Handle case of a corrupt last record, whose claimed length                                                                                                       
                             189:            //  would take us passed the end of the file                                                                                                                        
                             190:            if(start + len > b.length ) {                                                                                                                                       
                             191:                LOG.atWarn().log("Warning: Skipping record of type {} at position {} which claims to be longer than the file! ({} vs {})", type, box(start),                    
                             box(len), box(b.length - start));                                                                                                                                                   
                             192:                return null;                                                                                                                                                    
                             193:            }                                                                                                                                                                   
                             194:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             195:            throw new HSLFException("Couldn't instantiate the class for type with id " + type + " on class " + c + " : " + e, e);                                               
                             196:        }                                                                                                                                                                       
                             197:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             198:        // Handling for special kinds of records follow                                                                                                                         
                             199:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             200:        // If it's a position aware record, tell it where it is                                                                                                                 
                             ```                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             </code>                                                                                                                                                                             
                             <code>                                                                                                                                                                              
                             poi-scratchpad/src/main/java/org/apache/poi/hslf/usermodel/HSLFSlideShowImpl.java:250-316                                                                                           
                             ```                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             250:     */                                                                                                                                                                         
                             251:    private void buildRecords() throws IOException {                                                                                                                            
                             252:        // The format of records in a powerpoint file are:                                                                                                                      
                             253:        //   <little endian 2 byte "info">                                                                                                                                      
                             254:        //   <little endian 2 byte "type">                                                                                                                                      
                             255:        //   <little endian 4 byte "length">                                                                                                                                    
                             256:        // If it has a zero length, following it will be another record                                                                                                         
                             257:        //      <xx xx yy yy 00 00 00 00> <xx xx yy yy zz zz zz zz>                                                                                                             
                             258:        // If it has a length, depending on its type it may have children or data                                                                                               
                             259:        // If it has children, these will follow straight away                                                                                                                  
                             260:        //      <xx xx yy yy zz zz zz zz <xx xx yy yy zz zz zz zz>>                                                                                                             
                             261:        // If it has data, this will come straight after, and run for the length                                                                                                
                             262:        //      <xx xx yy yy zz zz zz zz dd dd dd dd dd dd dd>                                                                                                                  
                             263:        // All lengths given exclude the 8 byte record header                                                                                                                   
                             264:        // (Data records are known as Atoms)                                                                                                                                    
                             265:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             266:        // Document should start with:                                                                                                                                          
                             267:        //   0F 00 E8 03 ## ## ## ##                                                                                                                                            
                             268:        //     (type 1000 = document, info 00 0f is normal, rest is document length)                                                                                            
                             269:        //   01 00 E9 03 28 00 00 00                                                                                                                                            
                             270:        //     (type 1001 = document atom, info 00 01 normal, 28 bytes long)                                                                                                    
                             271:        //   80 16 00 00 E0 10 00 00 xx xx xx xx xx xx xx xx                                                                                                                    
                             272:        //   05 00 00 00 0A 00 00 00 xx xx xx                                                                                                                                   
                             273:        //     (the contents of the document atom, not sure what it means yet)                                                                                                  
                             274:        //   (records then follow)                                                                                                                                              
                             275:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             276:        // When parsing a document, look to see if you know about that type                                                                                                     
                             277:        //  of the current record. If you know it's a type that has children,                                                                                                   
                             278:        //  process the record's data area looking for more records                                                                                                             
                             279:        // If you know about the type and it doesn't have children, either do                                                                                                   
                             280:        //  something with the data (eg TextRun) or skip over it                                                                                                                
                             281:        // If you don't know about the type, play safe and skip over it (using                                                                                                  
                             282:        //  its length to know where the next record will start)                                                                                                                
                             283:        //                                                                                                                                                                      
                             284:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             285:        _records = read(_docstream, (int) currentUser.getCurrentEditOffset());                                                                                                  
                             286:    }                                                                                                                                                                           
                             287:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             288:    private Record[] read(byte[] docstream, int usrOffset) throws IOException {                                                                                                 
                             289:        //sort found records by offset.                                                                                                                                         
                             290:        //(it is not necessary but SlideShow.findMostRecentCoreRecords() expects them sorted)                                                                                   
                             291:        NavigableMap<Integer, Record> records = new TreeMap<>(); // offset -> record                                                                                            
                             292:        Map<Integer, Integer> persistIds = new HashMap<>(); // offset -> persistId                                                                                              
                             293:        initRecordOffsets(docstream, usrOffset, records, persistIds);                                                                                                           
                             294:        HSLFSlideShowEncrypted decryptData = new HSLFSlideShowEncrypted(docstream, records);                                                                                    
                             295:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             296:        for (Map.Entry<Integer, Record> entry : records.entrySet()) {                                                                                                           
                             297:            Integer offset = entry.getKey();                                                                                                                                    
                             298:            Record record = entry.getValue();                                                                                                                                   
                             299:            Integer persistId = persistIds.get(offset);                                                                                                                         
                             300:            if (record == null) {                                                                                                                                               
                             301:                // all plain records have been already added,                                                                                                                   
                             302:                // only new records need to be decrypted (tbd #35897)                                                                                                           
                             303:                decryptData.decryptRecord(docstream, persistId, offset);                                                                                                        
                             304:                record = Record.buildRecordAtOffset(docstream, offset);                                                                                                         
                             305:                entry.setValue(record);                                                                                                                                         
                             306:            }                                                                                                                                                                   
                             307:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             308:            if (record instanceof PersistRecord) {                                                                                                                              
                             309:                ((PersistRecord) record).setPersistId(persistId);                                                                                                               
                             310:            }                                                                                                                                                                   
                             311:        }                                                                                                                                                                       
                             312:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             313:        decryptData.close();                                                                                                                                                    
                             314:        return records.values().toArray(new Record[0]);                                                                                                                         
                             315:    }                                                                                                                                                                           
                             316:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             ```                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             </code>                                                                                                                                                                             
                             <code>                                                                                                                                                                              
                             poi-scratchpad/src/main/java/org/apache/poi/hslf/usermodel/HSLFSlideShowImpl.java:365-450                                                                                           
                             ```                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             365:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             366:    public DocumentEncryptionAtom getDocumentEncryptionAtom() {                                                                                                                 
                             367:        for (Record r : _records) {                                                                                                                                             
                             368:            if (r instanceof DocumentEncryptionAtom) {                                                                                                                          
                             369:                return (DocumentEncryptionAtom) r;                                                                                                                              
                             370:            }                                                                                                                                                                   
                             371:        }                                                                                                                                                                       
                             372:        return null;                                                                                                                                                            
                             373:    }                                                                                                                                                                           
                             374:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             375:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             376:    /**                                                                                                                                                                         
                             377:     * Find the "Current User" stream, and load it                                                                                                                              
                             378:     */                                                                                                                                                                         
                             379:    private void readCurrentUserStream() {                                                                                                                                      
                             380:        try {                                                                                                                                                                   
                             381:            currentUser = new CurrentUserAtom(getDirectory());                                                                                                                  
                             382:        } catch (IOException ie) {                                                                                                                                              
                             383:            LOG.atError().withThrowable(ie).log("Error finding Current User Atom");                                                                                             
                             384:            currentUser = new CurrentUserAtom();                                                                                                                                
                             385:        }                                                                                                                                                                       
                             386:    }                                                                                                                                                                           
                             387:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             388:    /**                                                                                                                                                                         
                             389:     * Find any other streams from the filesystem, and load them                                                                                                                
                             390:     */                                                                                                                                                                         
                             391:    private void readOtherStreams() {                                                                                                                                           
                             392:        // Currently, there aren't any                                                                                                                                          
                             393:    }                                                                                                                                                                           
                             394:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             395:    /**                                                                                                                                                                         
                             396:     * Find and read in pictures contained in this presentation.                                                                                                                
                             397:     * This is lazily called as and when we want to touch pictures.                                                                                                             
                             398:     */                                                                                                                                                                         
                             399:    private void readPictures() throws IOException {                                                                                                                            
                             400:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             401:        // if the presentation doesn't contain pictures, will use an empty collection instead                                                                                   
                             402:        if (!getDirectory().hasEntryCaseInsensitive("Pictures")) {                                                                                                              
                             403:            _pictures = new ArrayList<>();                                                                                                                                      
                             404:            return;                                                                                                                                                             
                             405:        }                                                                                                                                                                       
                             406:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             407:        final Entry en = getDirectory().getEntryCaseInsensitive("Pictures");                                                                                                    
                             408:        if (!(en instanceof DocumentEntry)) {                                                                                                                                   
                             409:            throw new IllegalArgumentException("Had unexpected type of entry for name: Pictures: " + en.getClass());                                                            
                             410:        }                                                                                                                                                                       
                             411:        DocumentEntry entry = (DocumentEntry) en;                                                                                                                               
                             412:        EscherContainerRecord blipStore = getBlipStore();                                                                                                                       
                             413:        byte[] pictstream;                                                                                                                                                      
                             414:        try (DocumentInputStream is = getDirectory().createDocumentInputStream(entry)) {                                                                                        
                             415:            pictstream = IOUtils.toByteArray(is, entry.getSize(), MAX_IMAGE_LENGTH);                                                                                            
                             416:        }                                                                                                                                                                       
                             417:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             418:        List<PictureFactory> factories = new ArrayList<>();                                                                                                                     
                             419:        try (HSLFSlideShowEncrypted decryptData = new HSLFSlideShowEncrypted(getDocumentEncryptionAtom())) {                                                                    
                             420:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             421:            int pos = 0;                                                                                                                                                        
                             422:            // An empty picture record (length 0) will take up 8 bytes                                                                                                          
                             423:            while (pos <= (pictstream.length - HSLFPictureData.PREAMBLE_SIZE)) {                                                                                                
                             424:                int offset = pos;                                                                                                                                               
                             425:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             426:                decryptData.decryptPicture(pictstream, offset);                                                                                                                 
                             427:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             428:                // Image signature                                                                                                                                              
                             429:                int signature = LittleEndian.getUShort(pictstream, pos);                                                                                                        
                             430:                pos += LittleEndianConsts.SHORT_SIZE;                                                                                                                           
                             431:                // Image type + 0xF018                                                                                                                                          
                             432:                int type = LittleEndian.getUShort(pictstream, pos);                                                                                                             
                             433:                pos += LittleEndianConsts.SHORT_SIZE;                                                                                                                           
                             434:                // Image size (excluding the 8 byte header)                                                                                                                     
                             435:                int imgsize = LittleEndian.getInt(pictstream, pos);                                                                                                             
                             436:                pos += LittleEndianConsts.INT_SIZE;                                                                                                                             
                             437:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             438:                // When parsing the BStoreDelay stream, [MS-ODRAW] says that we                                                                                                 
                             439:                //  should terminate if the type isn't 0xf007 or 0xf018->0xf117                                                                                                 
                             440:                if (!((type == 0xf007) || (type >= 0xf018 && type <= 0xf117))) {                                                                                                
                             441:                    break;                                                                                                                                                      
                             442:                }                                                                                                                                                               
                             443:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             444:                // The image size must be 0 or greater                                                                                                                          
                             445:                // (0 is allowed, but odd, since we do wind on by the header each                                                                                               
                             446:                //  time, so we won't get stuck)                                                                                                                                
                             447:                if (imgsize < 0) {                                                                                                                                              
                             448:                    throw new CorruptPowerPointFileException("The file contains a picture, at position " + factories.size() + ", which has a negatively sized                   
                             data length, so we can't trust any of the picture data");                                                                                                                           
                             449:                }                                                                                                                                                               
                             450:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             ```                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             </code>                                                                                                                                                                             
                             <code>

                             18:package org.apache.poi.hslf.usermodel;                                                                                                                                           
                             19:                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             20:import java.io.Closeable;                                                                                                                                                        
                             21:import java.io.IOException;                                                                                                                                                      
                             22:import java.io.OutputStream;                                                                                                                                                     
                             23:import java.security.GeneralSecurityException;

                             30:import org.apache.poi.EncryptedDocumentException;                                                                                                                                
                             31:import org.apache.poi.hslf.exceptions.CorruptPowerPointFileException;                                                                                                            
                             32:import org.apache.poi.hslf.exceptions.EncryptedPowerPointFileException;

                             35:import org.apache.poi.hslf.record.PositionDependentRecord;

                             37:import org.apache.poi.hslf.record.UserEditAtom;                                                                                                                                  
                             38:import org.apache.poi.hssf.record.crypto.Biff8EncryptionKey;                                                                                                                     
                             39:import org.apache.poi.poifs.crypt.ChunkedCipherInputStream;                                                                                                                      
                             40:import org.apache.poi.poifs.crypt.ChunkedCipherOutputStream;                                                                                                                     
                             41:import org.apache.poi.poifs.crypt.Decryptor;

                             43:import org.apache.poi.poifs.crypt.Encryptor;                                                                                                                                     
                             44:import org.apache.poi.util.BitField;                                                                                                                                             
                             45:import org.apache.poi.util.IOUtils;                                                                                                                                              
                             46:import org.apache.poi.util.Internal;                                                                                                                                             
                             47:import org.apache.poi.util.LittleEndian;                                                                                                                                         
                             48:import org.apache.poi.util.LittleEndianByteArrayInputStream;

                             51:                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             52:/**                                                                                                                                                                              
                             53: * This class provides helper functions for encrypted PowerPoint documents.                                                                                                      
                             54: */                                                                                                                                                                              
                             55:@Internal                                                                                                                                                                        
                             56:public class HSLFSlideShowEncrypted implements Closeable {                                                                                                                       
                             57:    DocumentEncryptionAtom dea;                                                                                                                                                  
                             58:    EncryptionInfo _encryptionInfo;
